FBIS4-29873 "dreas120_a_94014" FBIS-EAS-94-120 Daily Report 22 Jun 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Cabinet Members To Hold `Emergency' Meeting on Yen Cabinet Members To Hold `Emergency' Meeting on Yen OW2206025194 Tokyo KYODO in English 0246 GMT 22 Jun 94 OW2206025194 Tokyo KYODO English BFN [Text] Tokyo, June 22 KYODO -- Key cabinet members will meet at noon Wednesday [22 June] to discuss the yen's surge against the dollar and its possible dampening effects on the just-emerging recovery of the Japanese economy, government officials said. The yen soared to a new global postwar low of 99.85-95 yen in New York at one point Tuesday before finishing at 100.10-20 yen. The emergency cabinet meeting will discuss primarily the need to keep in close contact with other industrialized countries and jointly intervene in the currency markets to arrest the yen's ascent, the officials said . In addition, the meeting will reconfirm that no time should be lost in drafting a tax reforms program and other macroeconomic policies and deregulatory steps, they said. The noon meeting will bring together Prime Minister Tsutomu Hata, Finance Minister Hirohisa Fujii, Chief Cabinet Secretary Hiroshi Kumagai, and Yoshio Terasawa, director general of the Economic Planning Agency (EPA).
